<blue>1</blue><e5>Russia </e5>offers aid to help <e2>Mongolia </e2>fight extreme cold . <br><blue>2</blue><e5>Russia </e5>on Friday pledged to help <e2>Mongolia </e2>tackle the extreme cold weather that triggered a livestock disaster in the nation . <br><blue>3</blue><e4><eC>Russian </eC></e4><e4><eC>Prime </eC></e4><e4><eC>Minister </eC></e4><e4><eC>Vladimir </eC></e4><e4><eC>Putin </eC></e4>said <e5>Russia </e5>would provide 50,000 tons of wheat fodder to <e2>Mongolia </e2>, the Press and <e1>Information </e1><e1>Service </e1>of the <e2>Mongolian </e2>government reported . <br><blue>4</blue>The decision came after consultations with regional authorities of <e5>Russia </e5>, <e4>Putin </e4>said during a telephone conversation with <e4><eC>his </eC></e4><e2>Mongolian </e2><e6><eC>counterpart </eC></e6><e6><eC>Sukhbaataryn </eC></e6><e6><eC>Batbold </eC></e6>. <br><blue>5</blue><e6>Batbold </e6>thanked <e4>Putin </e4>on behalf of the <e2>Mongolian </e2>people and the government for paying attention to <e2>Mongolia </e2>'s efforts in fighting the natural disaster . <br><blue>6</blue>The prime ministers also exchanged views on <e3>Mongolia-Russia </e3>economic relations and bilateral cooperation . <br><blue>7</blue><e2>Mongolia </e2>has been hit by weeks of persistent snow and temperatures below minus 50 <e0>Celsius </e0>. <br><blue>8</blue>According to <e7>U.N. </e7>statistics , at least 2.7 million heads of livestock have been killed by cold weather in <e2>Mongolia </e2>. <br><blue>9</blue>The extreme weather also isolated herders and villages from food , fuel and medical care . <br></div>
